other.wheelchair:description: Dedicated Blue Badge spaces FREE (Dec 2015). RADAR key Toilet opposite Bancroft Road via light controlled crossing 100m to North
Blue Badge bays near store entrance. Steep slope to High Street. Level access to Bell Street. Accessible toilets in both store and Bell Street. Risk of flash flooding.
One Blue Badge space with tactile paving ramp
Was a pub car park, both redeveloped as housing = no car park. Will update OSM soon.
Can be muddy. No height limit, OK for minibus.  Access trail from here: http://www.surreycc.gov.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0009/29673/Colley-Hill-Easy-Access-trail.pdf
No dedicated spaces, electric vehicle charging point. Accessible WC beside cafe.
Day ticket parking from 9am. No dedicated Blue Badge spaces. Steep slope to station entrance.
2 dedicated Blue Badge spaces opposite entrance to Town Hall. Two more in car park extension at side.
No dedicated spaces, gravel sloping surface. Step-free to pub outdoor seating via access road.
Access to many all weather paths around lakes and golf course  nearby. Toilets replaced, no longer accessible, see latest 2018 photos.
One Blue Badge space beside entrance to platform 1. Free parking. Accessible WC was locked when I visited (6-18)
Blue Badge bays (NOT FREE) on level 1, but paypoint up a step!  Step-free exit via heavy door to east stairwell, or via access road with slope. Lift access to other floors difficult.
1 Blue Badge space, free parking. Step free route to Library.
2 dedicated Blue Badge spaces near Banstead Centre, 2 more opposite Library. Step-free routes to both. Charge applies.
Single dedicated Blue Badge space.
Dedicated Blue Badge spaces near entrance (Free at 5/2017). RingGo 5607
2 dedicated Blue Badge spaces opposite entrance. Level access to park, including Sensory Garden and cafe.
3 Dedicated Blue Badge spaces are the nearest to the entrance. WARNING: these bays slope towards wall.
No designated Blue Badge spaces. No ramp or dropped kerb to pavement
No dedicated Blue Badge spaces. Level asphalt surface.
Road to Centre door resurfaced 2/2017. Two dedicated Blue Badge spaces beside entrance ramp (New 5/2018). Accessible WC for Centre visitors.
1 Blue Badge space near entrance to supermarket and cash machine.
Pub being refurbished (6/2017) car park out of use
No dedicated Blue Badge spaces.
Nearest Blue Badge spaces near entrance from Upper West Street. Free for Blue Badge holders (9/2017)
Uneven cinder surface. Blue Badge bays against club house wall. Ramped entrance has been checked (fire exit route, no outside handles).
1 Dedicated Blue Badge space near exit.
No dedicated Blue Badge spaces discovered. Some spaces may be OK for non wheelchair users. Payment machine surrounded by kerb.
Sat, Sun & BH only. 2.2m barrier. No dedicated Blue Badge spaces. Steep route via roadway to street and Castle Grounds. Steps at south end towards Town Hall.

Dedicated Blue Badge bays are on a cross-slope between tree & building, below main entrance. May be difficult to safely transfer from vehicle to wheelchair/mobility scooter. Accessible toilet for customers inside Nutfield Lodge.
No blue badge bay. No ramp to footway.
No dedicated Blue Badge spaces in this section. Accessible toilet in Parish Centre via ramp.
2x Blue Badge spaces, accessible toilet via ramp  in Parish Centre opposite.
4 spaces FREE for Blue Badge holders. Step free, via ramp to ticket machine and platform 2 only - to/from London, and towards Reading.
